  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Uncertainty quantification was performed via Monte Carlo propagation of material property and geometric tolerances. A screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to identify influential parameters; results are summarized in the UQ report narrative. The dominant input drivers were informally ranked by analysts, and the UQ bounds reflect their judgment, but no structured sensitivity analysis object has been linked to this package.",
