      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters sourced from lot-specific measurements or certified material test reports; distributions characterized for UQ propagation.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and ultimate strength sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon data (n=5 per lot). Screw and rod outer diameters measured via CMM on production hardware. Distributions (mean, standard deviation) characterized for all primary inputs and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ. A screening sensitivity study conducted during model development informally identified elastic modulus and rod diameter as the most influential parameters; this ranking informed the UQ sampling strategy and is discussed in the UQ narrative report. The structured sensitivity analysis supporting this ranking has not been separately encoded as a linked analysis object in this package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
